posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked: I don’t see any obvious physical damage, so it’s probably dead. The jumper is for devices you connect to the NavX, so it shouldn’t matter.

accepted_answer.excerpt:
Looks like its physically ok so it is just dead.  The pin jumper sets the voltage on the additional DIO pins the NavX provides.  It doesn’t affect its base functionality. 
Sorry.
